                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>1 papyrus ; 27 x 19.1 cm.</support>
                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">Dark brown papyrus in bad condition of a bad quality; a big portion is lost at the lower side to the left; it has margins at all sides; a vertical strip of fibers has been removed ca. 3 cm from the left. It seems that the papyrus was randomly folded. Fibers are frayed, misaligned, removed or folded at the several parts; there is a lacuna at the middle, ca. 4 cm from the top edge. There are three small fragments are split off, mostly from the middle. There is a kollesis at the top can be seen on verso.</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">9</ab>
                           <ab type="recto-verso">Source of description: Recto</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Written across the fibers after rotate the papyrus 90 degrees in black ink with a thick nib; practiced hand wrote in medium-sized cursive with ligatures; the interlinear spaces are even of ca. 0.7 cm. the hand is characterized by two loops beta; rho with a half circle and at the top of vertical stroke ended with a hook; alpha mostly formed with tow loops. No diacritical marks. There is a huge blank area of ca. 9.5 cm at the end of the text.</p>
                  </handDesc>
